Package com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array.numbers

Interface FillingArrayNumbers<T extends java.lang.Number>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the numerical data stored and filled into an array.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Filling<Array<T>>, FillingArray<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FillingArrayRandomDoubleNumbers, FillingArrayRandomIntegerNumbers, FillingArrayReadDoubleNumbers, FillingArrayReadIntegerNumbers, FillingArraySequentialAscendingDecimalDigitOfDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialAscendingDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialAscendingIntegerNumbers, FillingArraySequentialDescendingDecimalDigitOfDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialDescendingDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialDescendingIntegerNumbers
    public interface FillingArrayNumbers<T extends java.lang.Number>
extends FillingArray<T>
    The interface that declares a contract to filling an array with numeric data.

    Also this interface is the inheritor of the FillingArray interface and thereby redefines its contract for filling with numeric data of an object of the Array wrapper class and an classical arrays.

    The numeric data by which the array can be filled are wrapper classes Array and must be the inheritance of the base class Number.

    Created by Konstantin Lugowoy on 08-Jan-18.

    Version:
    1.1
    Author:
    Konstantin Lugowoy
    See Also:
    Filling, FillingArray
